{
  "stem": "11290.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we felt that Munich was the big city, much, much bigger, also more international.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It had many students and visitors from foreign countries.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And people generally felt more freer there, that the Nazis were a little bit more cautious about what they did, at least at 1934, yet.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm only talking about 1934, which was the beginning.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, of course, it was a mistake, a big financial mistake, because we spent an enormous amount of money to move our business from-- from Nuremberg to Munich.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we even paid the moves of our employees, of which most of them followed us to Munich.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that was only for a few years, when it got just as bad there, because after 1938, after the Kristallnacht, the business had to be sold, which means 'sold' in quotation marks.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was taken over by an Aryan firm for very little money.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And actually only a token, but there was no choice.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It had to be.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were forced to do that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there must have been about 10 families, at least 10 families, that moved with us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And some of them decided not to move.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were actually the smart ones, because they rather refused to go, because it was only for a short time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But others may have been glad that they lived in Munich, which was-- was even during the war a better atmosphere than Nuremberg, Fuerth.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the life in Munich, I was only there from 1934 to 1936, when I went to America.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "These were two fairly good years-- we-- fairly good because we began to have our own cultural life.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Jewish community began to get itself together.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had our-- we were not allowed to go to any movies, any concerts.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
